CC ============================================================================
CC Corning HPFS Fused Silica catalog
CC ============================================================================
CC Built from Corning Specialty Materials Product Information Sheet
CC "HPFS 7979, 7980, 8655 Fused Silica", July 2015
CC Source: https://www.corning.com (Corning Advanced Optics)
CC
CC Catalog version: 1.1   (2026-05-16)
CC Compiled by Synapse Optics for use with LensHH-LT and other optical
CC design software supporting the Zemax AGF (Ascii Glass File) format.
CC
CC Sellmeier formula (Zemax/OpticStudio FormulaType 2):
CC     n^2 - 1 = K1 L^2/(L^2 - L1) + K2 L^2/(L^2 - L2) + K3 L^2/(L^2 - L3)
CC where L is wavelength in micrometers and L1, L2, L3 are the
CC wavelength-squared resonance terms (units of um^2).
CC
CC HPFS 7980 (22 C): coefficients are taken DIRECTLY from the Corning
CC brochure (3-term Sellmeier fit). Validation against the 20 tabulated
CC index values in the brochure yields a max error of 2.4e-06 over the
CC range 185 nm to 1129 nm.
CC
CC HPFS 7979 (22 C): the brochure provides a 4-term Sellmeier; the Zemax
CC AGF format only supports a 3-term Sellmeier (formula 2). The 3-term
CC coefficients below are a re-fit to the 35 tabulated indices in the
CC brochure (185 nm to 2326 nm). Max error 3.8e-06.
CC
CC HPFS 8655 (22 C): same situation as 7979. Coefficients are a 3-term
CC re-fit to indices generated from the brochure's 4-term 22 C Sellmeier
CC over 185 nm to 2326 nm. Max error 2.9e-06.
CC
CC All three glasses have:
CC   n_d (587.725 nm) = 1.458461 (7980), 1.458522 (7979, 8655)
CC   V_d              = 67.8
CC   density          = 2.20 g/cm^3
CC   thermal expansion alpha (-30 to +70 C) = 0.52 ppm/C
CC
CC Disclaimer: This catalog is provided as a convenience for optical
CC design and modeling. Always verify against the latest Corning
CC datasheet for production designs. No warranty is expressed or implied.
CC
CC ============================================================================
CC
CC NM  <name> <formula> <MIL> <Nd> <Vd> <ExcludeSubs> <Status> <MeltFreq>
CC ED  <TCE-30/70> <TCE+20/300> <density> <dPgF> <ignore_thermal_exp> <Status>
CC CD  <K1> <L1> <K2> <L2> <K3> <L3> 0 0 0 0
CC TD  six dn/dT coefficients + reference temperature
CC OD  six environmental data
CC LD  <lambda_min> <lambda_max>     in micrometers
CC IT  <wavelength_um> <int_trans> <thickness_mm>
CC
CC NM-line slot meaning (per OpticStudio "Glass Catalog Format"):
CC   MIL          = MIL-spec catalog number; use 0 if not applicable.
CC   Nd           = refractive index at d-line (587.56 nm), 1.0-2.0 typical.
CC   Vd           = Abbe number at d-line, > 0.
CC   ExcludeSubs  = 1 to exclude from glass substitution, else 0.
CC   Status       = 0 standard, 1 preferred, 2 obsolete, 3 special, 4 melt,
CC                  5 inquire, 6 experimental.
CC   MeltFreq     = melt frequency, 0..n (informational).
CC
CC IMPORTANT — ED-line last field MUST be 0 (not 1) in current OpticStudio.
CC Setting it to 1 ("Preferred") on a Sellmeier/Conrady glass causes
CC OpticStudio to silently mishandle the dispersion formula: the
CC prescription report shows the correct |n| but cardinal-point /
CC ray-trace evaluation uses a model-glass approximation that gives a
CC very different index and wrong EFL. Empirically verified 2026-05-14.
CC
CC ============================================================================
NM HPFS_7980 2 0 1.458461 67.80 0 0 1
ED 0.520000 0.570000 2.200000 0.000000 0 0
CD 0.683740494 0.004603528 0.420323613 0.013396886 0.585027480 64.493273200 0 0 0 0
TD 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 22.000000
OD -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000
LD 0.184950 1.128950
IT 0.184950 0.5000 25.000000
IT 0.193000 0.7000 10.000000
IT 0.214506 0.8500 10.000000
IT 0.248000 0.9990 10.000000
IT 0.365119 0.9999 10.000000
IT 0.587725 0.9999 10.000000
IT 1.014260 0.9999 10.000000
IT 1.128950 0.9990 10.000000
CC
CC ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC HPFS_7980 vendor-name aliases for vendor .zmx file compatibility
CC ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC The Edmund Optics vendor .zmx files use legacy/colloquial Corning HPFS
CC names in their GLAS field. Each alias below duplicates the HPFS_7980
CC Sellmeier coefficients verbatim under a different NM name, so the
CC glass resolver returns the canonical HPFS_7980 index data when a
CC vendor file references one of these aliases.
CC
CC Aliases added 2026-05-16:
CC   C79-80    -- legacy Corning product designation for HPFS 7980 used
CC                in Edmund's vendor .zmx (e.g. catalogs/Lenses/EdmundOptics
CC                /UVFSPlanoConvex/*.zmx). 493 surface uses in the
CC                May-2026 Edmund scrape (per glass-coverage-survey.json).
CC   F_SILICA  -- generic "fused silica" placeholder used by some Edmund
CC                .zmx files. 10 surface uses.
CC   FUSED     -- another generic "fused silica" placeholder. 1 surface use.
CC   SILICA    -- generic "silica" placeholder. 8 surface uses. Added 2026-05-17.
CC
CC If your vendor file actually references HPFS 7979 (which has slightly
CC different OH-content and a 4-term Sellmeier) or HPFS 8655 (low-OH grade),
CC use those entries directly instead of these aliases.
CC ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM C79-80 2 0 1.458461 67.80 0 0 1
GC Alias for HPFS_7980 (Corning legacy product code "Code 7980")
ED 0.520000 0.570000 2.200000 0.000000 0 0
CD 0.683740494 0.004603528 0.420323613 0.013396886 0.585027480 64.493273200 0 0 0 0
TD 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 22.000000
OD -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000
LD 0.184950 1.128950
CC
NM F_SILICA 2 0 1.458461 67.80 0 0 1
GC Alias for HPFS_7980 (generic "fused silica" vendor placeholder)
ED 0.520000 0.570000 2.200000 0.000000 0 0
CD 0.683740494 0.004603528 0.420323613 0.013396886 0.585027480 64.493273200 0 0 0 0
TD 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 22.000000
OD -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000
LD 0.184950 1.128950
CC
NM FUSED 2 0 1.458461 67.80 0 0 1
GC Alias for HPFS_7980 (generic "fused" vendor placeholder)
ED 0.520000 0.570000 2.200000 0.000000 0 0
CD 0.683740494 0.004603528 0.420323613 0.013396886 0.585027480 64.493273200 0 0 0 0
TD 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 22.000000
OD -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000
LD 0.184950 1.128950
CC
NM SILICA 2 0 1.458461 67.80 0 0 1
GC Alias for HPFS_7980 (generic "silica" vendor placeholder)
ED 0.520000 0.570000 2.200000 0.000000 0 0
CD 0.683740494 0.004603528 0.420323613 0.013396886 0.585027480 64.493273200 0 0 0 0
TD 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 22.000000
OD -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000 -1.000000
LD 0.184950 1.128950
CC
CC ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC
NM HPFS_7979 2 0 1.458522 67.80 0 0 1
ED 0.520000 0.570000 2.200000 0.000000 0 0
CD 0.679531453 0.004559592 0.424735954 0.013367126 0.908891753 99.382440947 0 0 0 0
